{
    "elem.1.38": {
        "id": "elem.1.38",
        "n": 38,
        "type": "proposition",
        "enunciation": "Triangles which are on equal bases and in the same parallels are equal to one another.",
        "proof": [
            {
                "text": "Let `ABC`, `DEF` be triangles on equal bases `BC`, `EF` and in the same parallels `BF`, `AD`; I say that the triangle `ABC` is equal to the triangle `DEF`.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "ABC",
                    "DEF",
                    "BC",
                    "EF",
                    "BF",
                    "AD",
                    "ABC",
                    "DEF"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For let `AD` be produced in both directions to `G`, `H`; through `B` let `BG` be drawn parallel to `CA`, [elem.1.31] and through `F` let `FH` be drawn parallel to `DE`.",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.31"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "AD",
                    "G",
                    "H",
                    "B",
                    "BG",
                    "CA",
                    "F",
                    "FH",
                    "DE"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Then each of the figures `GBCA`, `DEFH` is a parallelogram; and `GBCA` is equal to `DEFH`;",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "GBCA",
                    "DEFH",
                    "GBCA",
                    "DEFH"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "for they are on equal bases `BC`, `EF` and in the same parallels `BF`, `GH`. [elem.1.36]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.36"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "BC",
                    "EF",
                    "BF",
                    "GH"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Moreover the triangle `ABC` is half of the parallelogram `GBCA`; for the diameter `AB` bisects it. [elem.1.34]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.34"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "ABC",
                    "GBCA",
                    "AB"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And the triangle `FED` is half of the parallelogram `DEFH`; for the diameter `DF` bisects it. [elem.1.34]",
                "refs": [
                    "elem.1.34"
                ],
                "emphs": [
                    "FED",
                    "DEFH",
                    "DF"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "[But the halves of equal things are equal to one another.]",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the triangle `ABC` is equal to the triangle `DEF`.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": [
                    "ABC",
                    "DEF"
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore etc.",
                "refs": [],
                "emphs": []
            }
        ]
    }
}